  "body": "As a user, I want a dApp to be able to propose to me to switch the ethereum chain my wallet (and thus browser experience) is interacting with while I am browsing the dapps. \r\n\r\nMetamask will use this EIP to do this https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3085 and we should follow the same standard because it's de facto the one that dapps will use\r\n\r\nConsiderations:\r\n- security first. This is a sensitive feature and security considerations should be analysed in detail. See EIP-3085 for details https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3085\r\n\r\n\r\nWe should mimic metamask behavior when it comes to alerts:\r\n\r\n![confirmation-0](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1017008/179212574-132b3847-942d-4d86-ac3f-773ce77c7e82.png)\r\n\r\n![confirmation-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1017008/179212586-df4b049a-a420-47cd-8ad3-2a751e043062.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nChanging network without login/logout is currently not supported, but it's still worth working on this feature as it will eventually land in status-go.\r\nFor now, we should notify the user that it will require login/logout, and trigger a switch of network and login/logoutonce the network has been added.\r\n",
